  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is provided through correlation and goodness-of-fit metrics computed over the full operating envelope; these metrics present as rigorous but do not directly address the COU question of interest (worst-case hemolysis identification expressed as a relative hemolysis index RH < 1 against a predicate device).",
