    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels for MRL 2. Validation evidence demonstrates Pearson r = 0.961 and R² = 0.923 between CFD predictions and experimental haemolysis measurements across the 5-point operating envelope, with mesh convergence GCI of 2.1% and full iterative convergence confirmed. The 6 non-assessed factors are acceptable at MRL 2 per the ASME V&V 40 requirements matrix. The credibility assessment team concludes that sufficient evidence exists to accept the CFD model for the stated COU: identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device with RH < 1 relative to the predicate device.",
